---json
{
  "layout": "layouts/t-mofu.njk",
  "permalink": "/accounting/services/outsourced-accounting/",
  "slug": "acct-outsourced",
  "tierClass": "section--tier-guide",
  "bodyClass": "page--mofu",
  "callBar": true,
  "title": "Outsourced Accounting Services · TechBrot",
  "description": "Outsourced accounting services by Certified ProAdvisors — your full operational accounting function (bookkeeping, close, reconciliation, reporting, optional controller) run as a managed service on a fixed monthly fee. CPA-ready, no internal team to hire.",
  "breadcrumb": [
    { "name": "Home", "href": "/" },
    { "name": "Accounting", "href": "/accounting/" },
    { "name": "Services", "href": "/accounting/services/" },
    { "name": "Outsourced Accounting" }
  ],
  "hero": {
    "eyebrow": "Services · Outsourced accounting",
    "heading": "Your whole accounting function. Run for you.",
    "subheading": "Not just bookkeeping &mdash; the entire operational accounting department: transactions, reconciliation, month-end close, financial statements, payroll and sales-tax coordination, with controller oversight on top when you need it. TechBrot&rsquo;s Certified ProAdvisors run it as a managed service on a fixed monthly fee, CPA-ready, with no internal team to hire, train, or supervise. Independent firm, not affiliated with Intuit Inc.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=accounting", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Get the free file review", "href": "/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review", "class": "btn--ghost" },
      { "label": "Speak to a ProAdvisor", "tel": true, "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  },
  "inBrief": {
    "text": "<strong>Outsourced accounting</strong> means delegating your operational accounting function to an external firm instead of building and managing it in-house &mdash; recurring bookkeeping, the month-end close, account reconciliation, financial statement preparation, and coordination of payroll and sales tax, with optional controller oversight on top. The output is CPA-ready and handed to your tax professional for filing; TechBrot doesn&rsquo;t file taxes or perform audits, which keeps your books with accounting specialists and your returns with a licensed tax pro. Delivered by Certified ProAdvisors in your own QuickBooks file, on a fixed monthly fee, with a named lead and built-in continuity &mdash; a managed accounting department without the hiring, training, turnover, or single-person risk.",
    "source": "Reviewed by the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team at TechBrot Inc., an independent firm &mdash; not affiliated with Intuit Inc. Delivers the operational accounting function and coordinates with your CPA; not tax-filing, audit, or assurance services."
  },
  "ctaBand": {
    "eyebrow": "Ready when you are",
    "heading": "Hand off the whole function.",
    "lede": "Book a 30-minute discovery call. We&rsquo;ll review your current setup, what the function needs to cover, and whether outsourced accounting &mdash; or a cleanup first &mdash; is the right next step. Written fixed-fee scope within 3 business days. No pitch.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=accounting", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Explore Services", "href": "/accounting/services/", "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  }
}
---

<section class="section" id="acct-outsourced-definition">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">In plain terms</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Outsourced accounting, plainly.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      {%- for p in definition %}<p>{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="acct-outsourced-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Outsourced accounting, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <p class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</p>
        <div class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="acct-outsourced-included">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What&rsquo;s included</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">The whole function &mdash; not a slice of it.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Outsourced accounting bundles the operational layers into one managed service. Each is a discipline in its own right; together they&rsquo;re your accounting department.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for d in deliverables %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <p class="num">{{ d.num }}</p>
        <h3>{{ d.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ d.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="acct-outsourced-signals">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">When outsourcing the function makes sense</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">If any of these sound familiar, the answer is probably yes.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Most owners reach for outsourced accounting when running the function internally costs more &mdash; in money, time, or risk &mdash; than it returns.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for s in signals %}
      <div class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__opener">{{ s.opener | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="acct-outsourced-vs">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Outsourced vs in-house</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">The real cost of an internal accounting department.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      {%- for p in vsInHouse %}<p>{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="acct-outsourced-process">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">How it works</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">From handoff to a function that just runs.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Four phases, fixed monthly fee, written scope, your own QuickBooks file.</p>
    </header>
    <ol class="process-diagram">
      {%- for s in process %}
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">{{ s.num | safe }}</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">{{ s.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      </li>
      {%- endfor %}
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="acct-outsourced-scope">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Honest scope</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What the managed function covers &mdash; and what stays with your CPA.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for c in scope %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <h3>{{ c.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ c.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="acct-outsourced-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">FAQ</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Outsourced accounting questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="acct-outsourced-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="acct-outsourced-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    {%- for item in faqExtra %}
    <div class="prose" id="acct-outsourced-faq-x{{ loop.index }}">
      <h3>{{ item.q | safe }}</h3>
      <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
    </div>
    {%- endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="acct-outsourced-review">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Page review &amp; standards</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Reviewed by the ProAdvisor team.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>This page reflects how TechBrot delivers outsourced accounting. It is maintained by the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team at TechBrot Inc., a Delaware-incorporated independent ProAdvisor firm, and reviewed for accuracy on the scope of the managed function, the in-house comparison, and the boundary with licensed CPA and tax work. Where our approach or scope changes, this page is updated. Outsourced accounting is delivered in your own QuickBooks file on a fixed monthly fee and coordinated with your CPA for filing and any formal CPA engagement.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in reviewSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="in-brief__source">Page last reviewed: May 2026.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="acct-outsourced-related">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Related</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Related services.</h2>
    </header>
    {%- for n in related %}
    <div class="stack-8">
      <h3><a href="{{ n.href }}">{{ n.title | safe }}</a></h3>
      <p class="prose">{{ n.body | safe }}</p>
    </div>
    {%- endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
